Title: Lectures on D-branes

Comments: Latex file, 61 pages, 8 figures. Based on lectures given in 1997 at

the Isaac Newton Institute, Cambridge, the Trieste Spring School on StringTheory, and at the 31rst International Symposium Ahrenshoop in Buckow. Someextra comments and added references. Final version to appear in proceedingsThis is an introduction to the physics of D-branes. Topics covered includePolchinski's original calculation, a critical assessment of some dualitychecks, D-brane scattering, and effective worldvolume actions.